member.name: M:Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.TestAuto.LoggingAndSharedGenericMethods.ProcessTestData(System.String,System.String)
member.summary: Processes test data
member.returns: Processed Test Data to be used by Test

remarks.para: $PROCESS: is used to indicate that the xml value is to be processed.
[TODAY,+] or [TODAY,-]: Todays date without time incremented or decremented by SECONDS, MINUTES,HOURS,MONTHS, DAYS or YEARS.
[TODAY,+,< formatString >] or [TODAY,-,< formatString >]: Same as above but format string can be explicitly defined.
Sample xml fragments and processed values:
$PROCESS:[SPACES,1] this is used when we just want to have spaces as the value to use, the integer value represents the number of spaces to use
$PROCESS:[ENVIRONMENTVARIABLE,VariableName, DefaultValue] allows test to use values specified in environment variables when specified instead of the default
$PROCESS:[XPATH,xpath to some location data file] allows a data file to reference dynamic data from another section
